This paper is about natural language inference (NLI) models and their ability to perform monotonicity reasoning, which involves capturing the interaction between lexical and syntactic structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper also discusses the performance of state-of-the-art NLI models, indicating that it falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The use of neural networks in the models suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions data augmentation and analysis, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
